<item>
            <title>[WICKET-4584] NumberTextField does not have default minimum and maximum</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4584</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Javadoc of NumberTextField says:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A TextField for HTML5 &amp;lt;input&amp;gt; with type number.&lt;br/&gt;
Automatically validates the input against the configured min and max attributes. If any of them is null then Double.MIN_VALUE and Double.MAX_VALUE are used respectfully. Note: FormComponent.setType(Class) must be called explicitly!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is not true. We have constructor which sets them to null:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	public NumberTextField(String id, IModel&amp;lt;N&amp;gt; model, Class&amp;lt;N&amp;gt; type)&lt;/p&gt;
	{
		super(id, model, type);

		validator = null;
		minimum = null;
		maximum = null;
	}

&lt;p&gt;and if I don&apos;t set them manually, in case of error nulls go to RangeValidator (line 84-85:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;			error.setVariable(&quot;minimum&quot;, min);&lt;br/&gt;
			error.setVariable(&quot;maximum&quot;, max);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;causing:&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Argument &apos;value&apos; may not be null.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nevertheless, I think reflection API should be used to determine if given Number has MAX_VALUE/MIN_VALUE and this one should be used. In other case I think it is ok to use Double.MAX_VALUE/MIN_VALUE.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or maybe you have another ideas?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
